`crates/` is a Cargo workspace root containing a single member, `steno`, the `.steno`-to-Plover-dictionary compiler and its LSP/editor tooling. Depending on this workspace means depending on `steno/src/`'s pipeline (`parse` â†’ `expand` â†’ `render`/`snippet`/`blocks`) or its three standalone binaries; there is currently no other crate to coordinate with, so no cross-crate coupling, shared-version, or workspace-manifest concern exists at this level.

All substantive facts â€” the compiler pipeline, its shared subsystems, the `dict.steno` test-fixture entanglement, the `TypedEntry` layout landmine, and the binaries' independent workspace-root handling â€” live in `steno/rollup.ctx` and are not restated here. A change touching the workspace `Cargo.toml` (adding a member, bumping shared dependency versions) is the only kind of edit that would originate at this level rather than inside `steno/`.

No `intent.md` exists for this directory, so no divergence to report.